section.t:
As described in  there are several common peering relations between eBGP sessions:

  Provider - sender is a transit provider to neighbor;
  Customer - sender is customer of neighbor;
  RS - sender is route server at internet exchange point (IX)
  RS-client - sender is client of RS at internet exchange point (IX)
  Peer - sender and neighbor are peers;

The RLD community MUST follow next semantics:

  4200000000 - suggested class for well-known transit large communities;
  1 - RLD subclass;
  value - ASN who set the community

This community MUST be set if route is announced to Customer, RS-client or Peer with ASN value equal to sender.

To address this issue we introduce another well-known BGP community Route Leak Notification (RLN).
It has next semantics:

  4200000000 - suggested class for well-known large communities;
  2 - RLN subclass;
  value - ASN who set the community

